What are User Roles?

A Role defines what a user is allowed to do inside Odoo.

Common roles include:

Sales User
Sales Manager
Purchase User
Inventory User
Accountant
HR Manager
Administrator

Each role grants different permissions.

Access Rights

Access Rights determine what actions a user can perform.

Permissions include:

Create
Read
Write (Edit)
Delete

Example:

Salesperson

Create Quotations
Edit Own Quotations
View Customers

Sales Manager

Manage All Sales Orders
Approve Quotations
View Reports
Security Groups

Security Groups are collections of permissions assigned to users.

Examples:

Sales
Inventory
Accounting
Purchase
Human Resources

A user can belong to one or more groups depending on their job responsibilities.

Assigning Users to Companies

Users can be assigned to one or multiple companies.

Example:

Sales Manager

Allowed Companies:

ABC Supermarket
ABC Textile Store

Default Company:

ABC Supermarket

This ensures users work only within authorized companies.

Record Rules

Record Rules control which records a user can access.

Example:

Salesperson

Can view only their own quotations.

Sales Manager

Can view all quotations created by the sales team.

This protects sensitive business information.

User Permission Example
Salesperson

Can:

Create Quotations
View Own Customers
Update Own Sales Orders

Cannot:

Delete Sales Orders
Change User Permissions
Access Accounting
Sales Manager

Can:

Manage Sales Team
Approve Quotations
View Sales Reports
Access All Sales Orders
Administrator

Can:

Create Users
Assign Roles
Configure Settings
Install Applications
Manage All Modules

Administrators have complete control over the Odoo system.

Benefits of Proper Access Rights
Protects business data
Prevents unauthorized access
Improves security
Reduces user errors
Supports company policies
Ensures compliance
Best Practices
Create separate login accounts for every employee.
Assign only the permissions required for each role.
Review user access regularly.
Remove inactive users.
Use strong passwords.
Restrict Administrator access to authorized personnel only.
